Bring a large #pot{} of water to the boil. Roughly chop the @mint leaves{1/2}. Place
the flat side of a large #knife{} on the @garlic{2%cloves} and press down firmly.
Peel off the skin and finely chop.

Cook the @wheat penne pasta{200%g} in the boiling water for ~{10%mins} with a
pinch of @salt{pinch}.

> Tip: Reserve some of the pasta water before you drain it, you might need it
> later on!

Brown off the @pine nuts{2} in a #non-stick frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

> Tip: They should take a few mins to start browning but watch them like a
> hawk as they can burn really easily.

Once toasted take them out of the pan and keep them for later.

Heat a small splash of @olive oil{} in the same pan on medium-high heat. Cook
the @pancetta{1%pack}(British smoked bacon lardons) until it goes crispy around
the edges.

Add in the @peas{1%pack} and continue to cook for ~{5%mins}. Add in your garlic
and fry for a further ~{1%minute}.

Now add a splash of water from your pasta to the pan with your peas and
pancetta. Cook for ~{1%minute} before stirring in the @crème fraîche{1%pack}
together with the @vegetable stock pot{1/2} and a few good grinds of
@black pepper{}.

By now your pasta should be ready. Drain it and mix into your sauce together
with your chopped mint.

Plate up your pasta, grate the @parmesan cheese{2} over the top and sprinkle
over your pine nuts. Tuck in and enjoy!